REM PILOT Example Program - Hello World with Turtle Graphics
REM This program demonstrates basic PILOT commands and turtle graphics

L:START
T:ðŸŽ¨ Welcome to TimeWarp PILOT Programming!
T:Let's draw some shapes with turtle graphics!

REM Draw a square
T:Drawing a square...
U:SIZE=50
T:FORWARD *SIZE*
T:RIGHT 90
T:FORWARD *SIZE*
T:RIGHT 90
T:FORWARD *SIZE*
T:RIGHT 90
T:FORWARD *SIZE*
T:RIGHT 90

REM Move to new position
T:Moving to draw a triangle...
T:PENUP
T:FORWARD 100
T:PENDOWN

REM Draw a triangle
T:Drawing a triangle...
U:SIDES=3
U:ANGLE=120
T:FORWARD 60
T:RIGHT *ANGLE*
T:FORWARD 60
T:RIGHT *ANGLE*
T:FORWARD 60
T:RIGHT *ANGLE*

REM Interactive section
T:Now let's get interactive!
A:NAME
T:Hello *NAME*! Thanks for trying PILOT programming!

REM Math example
U:X=15
U:Y=25
U:SUM=*X*+*Y*
T:*X* + *Y* = *SUM*

T:Program completed! Try modifying the SIZE and SIDES variables.
END</content>
